// GAP #7 (2026-04-19 audit)
// CLAIM: `defer` nested inside another `defer` body should be a
//        parse error (per the design notes: "defer inside defer
//        body is parse-rejected").
// EFFECT: compiler accepts it. Inner defer runs at outer-defer
//         execution time, which is at outer scope exit. Semantics
//         confusing and probably not what the programmer intends.
// FIX APPROACH: in check_stmt NODE_DEFER, check `c->defer_depth > 0`
//               and emit "defer cannot be nested inside defer
//               body" error. ~5 lines.

u32 main() {
    defer {
        defer { u32 x = 1; }    // should be compile error
    }
    return 0;
}
